Find $9^{-1} \pmod{100}$, as a residue modulo 100.  (Give an answer between 0 and 99, inclusive.)
inference: We want to find an integer $x$ such that $9x \equiv 1 \pmod{100}$.  Notice that $9 \cdot 11 = 99 \equiv -1 \pmod{100}$.  Multiplying both sides by $-1$, we get $9 \cdot (-11) \equiv 1 \pmod{100}$, so $9^{-1} \equiv -11 \equiv \boxed{89} \pmod{100}$. Final Answer: $\boxed{89}$. I hope it is correct.
